# Incident Report – Case 02: Amazon Delivery Phishing Email

## Time of Activity
05/25/2026 02:33:48.320

---

## Summary
A phishing email impersonating Amazon delivery services attempted to redirect the user to a shortened malicious URL. Firewall logs confirmed the connection attempt was blocked.

---

## Affected Entities
- Sender: urgents@amazon.biz
- Recipient: h.harris@thetrydaily.thm
- URL: http://bit.ly/3sHkX3da12340
- Destination IP: 67.199.248.11
- Source IP: 10.20.2.17

---

## Investigation Steps
- Searched email logs for sender reputation
- Validated absence of legitimate Amazon purchase history
- Checked VirusTotal reputation (1/92 malicious flag)
- Correlated firewall logs for URL access attempt

---

## Key Findings
- Fake Amazon domain used (amazon.biz)
- URL shortening service used for obfuscation
- Connection attempt blocked by firewall policy
- No endpoint execution observed

---

## Conclusion
True Positive – phishing attempt blocked at network layer

---

## Escalation Decision
No escalation required (blocked at perimeter)

---

## Remediation Actions
- Block sender domain
- Add URL to threat intel blacklist
- User awareness training on phishing links

---

## Indicators of Compromise (IOCs)
- bit.ly link
- amazon.biz domain
- 67.199.248.11
